# Allowlist build context: ignore everything, then re-include only what the
# Dockerfile actually COPYs. Keeps .env (tunnel token), .git, .claude, the
# compose file, and docs out of the build context entirely — smaller/faster
# builds and no stray secrets handed to the Docker daemon.
#
# How it works: `*` excludes every top-level entry; each `!` line un-ignores
# one. Re-including the `files` directory brings its whole subtree along.
*
!files
!nginx.conf
